Database consistency checks
Cleanup old backups



Rebuild Indexes: Recreating a table's indexes from scratch to eliminate fragmentation, reclaim disk space, and restore optimal search speeds.

Update Statistics: Refreshing the database engine's internal data distribution maps so the query optimizer can choose the fastest execution paths.

Database Consistency Checks: Running low-level structural integrity scans (like DBCC CHECKDB) to catch internal allocation errors or data corruption early.

Cleanup Old Backups: Automatically purging expired backup files and history records from storage disks to prevent drives from running out of space.
